-- Orban Says He Will Heed EU Criticism When Needed, Bild Reports
-- B y   R a i n e r   B u e r g i n
-- 2012-01-19T07:38:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-19/orban-says-he-will-heed-eu-criticism-when-needed-bild-reports.html
Hungarian Prime Minister  Viktor Orban  promised to heed European Union criticism when needed on
issues including the staffing of the country’s central bank,
 Germany ’s  Bild-Zeitung  said, citing an interview.  Orban said he’ll “bow to the weight of the arguments” as
long as critics of  Hungary  keep to the facts, Bild reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
